losing weight during the first trimester ok i've heard about women losing weight throughout the whole pregnancy but i always thought that they kept getting bigger even with the weight loss but i'm weeks along and i've actually lost weight and dropped a size i've never heard of this not that i'm really complaining but should i be worried about how the baby is growing don't worry the baby takes what nutrients it needs from you whether by way of the food you eat or by breaking down your excess fat and muscle as long as you are still a healthy weight losing a few pounds is usually not an issue especially in the first trimester just keep taking those prenatal vitamins Pregnancy Dieting Breastfeeding Obstetrics Tocopherol Coeliac disease Atkins Nutritional Approach Folic acid Bodybuilding Milk Prenatal care Urinary incontinence Vitamin Miscarriage Obesity Anorexia nervosa Guinea pig Weight training Omega-3 fatty acid Adjustable gastric band Vitamin C Super Size Me Veganism Nutrition Abortion debate Birth weight Weight loss Binge eating disorder Childbirth Egg (food) Human height Liver Anemia Abortion in the United States Cystic fibrosis Prenatal diagnosis Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Diarrhea Roe v. Wade Puberty Amniotic sac Insulin Breech birth Androgen insensitivity syndrome Prostate cancer Intact dilation and extraction Diabetes mellitus Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Equine conformation Osteoporosis Hyperemesis gravidarum B vitamins Garfield Melanie Wilkes Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Nutrient Rush Limbaugh Elvis and Me South Beach diet Raw food diet Morning sickness Carpal tunnel syndrome Friends Brown Bear EastEnders Abortion Midwifery Protein-energy malnutrition Atherosclerosis Cancer Hamster Domestic rabbit Body mass index Coronary heart disease Low-carbohydrate diet Garlic Clinical depression Sudden infant death syndrome Weight Watchers In vitro fertilisation Cheese Exercise Healthy eating Comanche Ron and Fez Muscle Abortion in Canada Vegetarian 